WEBVTT

00:09.792 --> 00:12.708
[♪♪♪]

00:15.333 --> 00:18.208
[electricity buzzing]

00:28.833 --> 00:31.750
[♪♪♪]

00:39.208 --> 00:42.125
[♪♪♪]

00:49.208 --> 00:52.125
[dramatic music]

00:58.333 --> 01:00.208
[man] [voice-over]
I was telling you at dinner

01:00.208 --> 01:03.292
that I believe that money,
clothes, adulation, et cetera,

01:03.292 --> 01:05.125
was a necessity with you.

01:05.125 --> 01:07.333
That some people are impelled
towards an objective

01:07.333 --> 01:09.458
without even consciously
knowing why.

01:09.458 --> 01:12.250
-Is there something criminal
in my being ambitious?

01:12.250 --> 01:15.833
-[chuckles] Why no, criminal?
Of course not.

01:15.833 --> 01:19.250
Unless your ambitions
take a perverse form,

01:19.250 --> 01:21.500
and you will stop at nothing,
right or wrong,

01:21.500 --> 01:23.167
to get what you want.

01:23.167 --> 01:25.125
-They say the female
of the species

01:25.125 --> 01:26.417
is deadlier than the male.

01:27.500 --> 01:28.750
[strikes a match]

01:31.292 --> 01:32.542
[older Aileen] [voice-over]
I guess I always did dream

01:32.542 --> 01:33.458
of being famous.

01:37.250 --> 01:39.875
Grew up watching them
glamorous movie stars

01:39.875 --> 01:42.167
and them black and white
pictures, you know.

01:43.750 --> 01:45.292
Lana Turner.

01:45.292 --> 01:46.458
Rita Hayworth.

01:46.458 --> 01:48.125
Barbara Stanwyck.

01:49.333 --> 01:50.750
They were hot.

01:57.708 --> 02:01.667
You all doing another
primetime special about me?

02:01.667 --> 02:03.292
-No, this will be
a documentary.

02:07.708 --> 02:11.292
-So, you wanna talk
about them seven pigs

02:11.292 --> 02:13.958
that I had to kill?

02:13.958 --> 02:15.750
[gunshot]

02:15.750 --> 02:16.958
[Peter] [voice-over]
You're known the world over.

02:16.958 --> 02:18.625
[gunshots]

02:18.625 --> 02:20.417
They call you Aileen Wuornos:

02:20.417 --> 02:21.750
[gunshot]

02:21.750 --> 02:23.750
"The Hooker From Hell",

02:23.750 --> 02:25.458
"The Damsel of Death".

02:25.458 --> 02:27.250
[car door opens]

02:27.250 --> 02:28.625
[older Aileen] [voice-over]
Personally, I like

02:28.625 --> 02:30.833
"Angel of Death".
Suits me better.

02:33.583 --> 02:34.875
-We were hoping
for something different.

02:36.875 --> 02:39.333
Something you've never discussed
in a previous interview before.

02:39.333 --> 02:40.792
-Shit, man.

02:40.792 --> 02:43.500
How many more times
do I gotta go through this?

02:43.500 --> 02:46.542
[scoffs] I guess not many,
since any day now,

02:46.542 --> 02:48.500
they'll be putting me down
like a rabid bitch.

02:48.500 --> 02:50.292
[Peter] Tomorrow, Aileen.

02:50.292 --> 02:52.500
Your execution is scheduled
for tomorrow.

02:52.500 --> 02:53.833
[flick of light switch]

02:57.667 --> 02:59.292
-So...

02:59.292 --> 03:02.333
Exclusive, huh?
Inside scoop?

03:05.833 --> 03:09.333
I bet you didn't know
that once upon a time,

03:09.333 --> 03:14.250
I was young and beautiful
and married.

03:14.250 --> 03:16.000
- Are you referring to
your rather brief marriage

03:16.000 --> 03:17.583
to a wealthy yacht club
president?

03:17.583 --> 03:19.750
-Commodore.
-Pardon me?

03:19.750 --> 03:21.750
-The head of a yacht club
ain't called a "President."

03:21.750 --> 03:23.292
He's called a "Commodore."

03:23.292 --> 03:24.708
Now, do you want to
hear this story or not?

03:24.708 --> 03:25.708
-I do apologize.

03:26.792 --> 03:27.875
Please, go ahead.

03:30.458 --> 03:33.375
Tell us about your marriage
to the Commodore.

03:34.917 --> 03:36.250
-You wanna hear a story?

03:37.375 --> 03:40.042
I'll give you a goddamn story.

03:40.042 --> 03:42.958
[rock music]

03:46.333 --> 03:47.542
[blood splattering]

03:47.542 --> 03:50.417
[rock music continues]

05:35.832 --> 05:39.832
[crickets stridulating]

05:39.832 --> 05:42.792
[Aileen groans]

05:45.957 --> 05:48.832
[Dewey moans]

05:54.000 --> 05:55.167
-What the fuck, bitch?

05:55.167 --> 05:56.917
-I said no mouth kissin.'

05:56.917 --> 06:00.792
-You said "everything."
I paid for everythin'.

06:00.792 --> 06:02.583
-Get off of me, motherfucker!
-[Dewey groans]

06:02.583 --> 06:04.417
[punches thrown]

06:04.417 --> 06:06.083
-Oh, what the fuck?!

06:06.083 --> 06:08.167
Fuck!

06:08.167 --> 06:09.792
What the fucking fuck?

06:09.792 --> 06:12.458
You knocked my fuckin'
tooth out, bitch!

06:12.458 --> 06:14.583
[Dewey groans]

06:14.583 --> 06:16.875
How the fuck am I supposed to
go home like this?

06:16.875 --> 06:18.417
Damn! My wife's gonna kill me!

06:18.417 --> 06:19.917
-Yeah, well,
tell her you got robbed.

06:22.582 --> 06:24.042
Here's what you're gonna do.

06:24.042 --> 06:26.707
You're gonna hand
your wallet real slow,

06:26.707 --> 06:29.542
and then you're gonna drive
the hell out of here real fast.

06:29.542 --> 06:32.500
-[chuckles]
You're a feisty one, ain'tcha?

06:32.500 --> 06:35.042
Well now, now you're gonna pay.

06:36.417 --> 06:39.042
-[slams head]
-[car horn blares]

06:43.750 --> 06:44.917
[older Aileen] [voice-over]
I was different

06:44.917 --> 06:46.125
back in those days, ya know?

06:46.125 --> 06:47.875
Real ignorant about life,

06:47.875 --> 06:49.042
a lot younger.

06:50.207 --> 06:52.250
Slightly prettier too, I guess.

06:52.250 --> 06:55.167
-[fireworks blasting]
-[military music playing]

07:30.582 --> 07:31.917
[fireworks whistling]

07:31.917 --> 07:33.000
[crowd gasping]

07:35.542 --> 07:37.707
[laughter and chatter]

07:38.792 --> 07:41.500
[Jennifer giggles]

07:44.917 --> 07:45.832
[Grady] Ooh.

07:49.250 --> 07:51.125
[Jennifer] Hey, there.

07:51.125 --> 07:52.707
What's your name?

07:52.707 --> 07:54.582
-Aileen.

07:54.582 --> 07:55.957
My friends call me Lee.

07:55.957 --> 07:58.625
-Well, good to meet you, Lee.
I'm Jennifer.

07:58.625 --> 08:00.750
My friends call me
Jen or Jenny.

08:00.750 --> 08:02.542
Take your pick. Come join us.

08:03.875 --> 08:04.917
Come on.

08:09.083 --> 08:11.000
Come on.

08:11.000 --> 08:12.875
Everybody, this is Lee.

08:12.875 --> 08:14.792
Lee, this is everybody.

08:14.792 --> 08:16.000
-Hi, Lee.
-Thanks.

08:16.000 --> 08:17.542
[Grady] How you doing?

08:17.542 --> 08:21.707
-It's a-- it's a real nice--
nice beach.

08:21.707 --> 08:25.625
[Grady] Nicest private beach
in Volusia County.

08:25.625 --> 08:27.500
And my pad's got the best view.

08:28.582 --> 08:30.957
So. where are you from?

08:30.957 --> 08:32.957
-Jesus, Grady. Lay off.

08:32.957 --> 08:34.625
[Grady] Lee and I are
just having some fun here,

08:34.625 --> 08:35.832
aren't we, Lee?

08:35.832 --> 08:37.167
[Aileen sniffs]

08:37.167 --> 08:39.167
That's a pretty manly name
you got there.

08:39.167 --> 08:40.167
"Lee."

08:42.207 --> 08:43.875
Did your daddy call you that
'cause he couldn't tell

08:43.875 --> 08:45.708
whether you were
a boy or a girl?

08:45.708 --> 08:47.708
-Grady, cut it out.
Mitch, can you do something.

08:47.708 --> 08:49.625
-Yeah. Cool out, man.
Leave her alone.

08:49.625 --> 08:52.208
-Momma took off and left you
when she found out

08:52.208 --> 08:54.583
you were nothing but
a big, pussy-eating dyke?

08:55.708 --> 08:57.000
-[Aileen grunts]
-[all yell]

08:57.000 --> 08:58.875
-[Jennifer] Oh, God!
-[Mitch] Oh, shit!

08:58.875 --> 09:01.083
[Aileen] You need to stop,
you motherfucker.

09:03.292 --> 09:05.250
-Get off him, get off him.
Relax. Hey, hey, hey.

09:05.250 --> 09:07.958
-You don't know
a goddamn thing about me.

09:07.958 --> 09:09.750
-[Grady spits]
-[Aileen panting]

09:12.750 --> 09:14.083
-[sobs] I'm sorry.

09:16.875 --> 09:18.875
I'm real sorry. I-I didn't
mean to ruin your party.

09:23.750 --> 09:25.125
-Hey, let me take you home.

09:25.125 --> 09:27.792
-Mitch? Okay.
-Yeah. Of course. Go.

09:27.792 --> 09:29.875
-[Jennifer] Hey, Lee.
-Lee, wait up.

09:29.875 --> 09:31.708
[Aileen] Leave me the hell
alone! I don't need no trouble.

09:31.708 --> 09:33.042
[Mitch] Are you ever
gonna grow the fuck up?

09:33.042 --> 09:34.875
-Really? Because I happen to

09:34.875 --> 09:37.250
think what you did back there
was totally fucking amazing.

09:37.250 --> 09:39.625
-What do you want from me?
-Nothing.

09:39.625 --> 09:42.875
Well, I guess I just
want to get to know you.

09:42.875 --> 09:45.375
Besides, once word about
what you did gets around,

09:45.375 --> 09:47.250
you're gonna be a hero
to all the girls

09:47.250 --> 09:49.708
who wish they'd had the courage
to stand up to him.

09:53.083 --> 09:54.875
Hey, you got a place to crash?

09:57.250 --> 09:59.208
Well, come stay the night
with me then.

09:59.208 --> 10:00.875
I've got some good weed at home.

10:00.875 --> 10:03.792
[fireworks blasting]

10:05.750 --> 10:08.667
[cheers and applause]

10:09.917 --> 10:12.833
[♪♪♪]

10:18.792 --> 10:20.750
Here's to the Bicentennial

10:20.750 --> 10:22.875
and the greatest country
in the world.

10:22.875 --> 10:24.917
-Land of opportunity.

10:26.708 --> 10:27.792
-Come on.

10:35.458 --> 10:37.250
[Jennifer] [voice-over]
I only came back 'cause

10:37.250 --> 10:40.000
you know,
my mom got sick last year.

10:40.000 --> 10:42.167
She, uh... she died
a couple months ago.

10:43.792 --> 10:45.042
Well, now my dad needs me,

10:45.042 --> 10:46.958
so, here I am.

10:46.958 --> 10:50.250
-♪ Love hurts ♪

10:50.250 --> 10:54.292
♪ Ooh ooh love hurts ♪

10:54.292 --> 10:56.000
-I hope you like Russian water.

10:59.125 --> 11:04.875
-♪ Some fools think
Of happiness ♪

11:04.875 --> 11:06.333
♪ Blissfulness togetherness ♪

11:06.333 --> 11:08.333
[Jennifer coughs]

11:08.333 --> 11:11.000
-Okay, so now
you have to tell me,

11:11.000 --> 11:13.333
where are you actually from?
-♪ Some fools fool... ♪

11:13.333 --> 11:15.500
-Mmm.
-...Themselves I guess ♪

11:15.500 --> 11:17.833
-Michigan.

11:17.833 --> 11:20.000
-Michigan?

11:20.000 --> 11:22.000
All right. Well...

11:22.000 --> 11:24.833
but do you still have
family or friends there?

11:24.833 --> 11:26.833
-Nah, I ain't got no ties.

11:26.833 --> 11:28.250
[Jennifer] Hmm.

11:28.250 --> 11:30.333
-None that I give
a damn about anyway.

11:32.208 --> 11:33.875
I mean, I do have a brother.

11:35.208 --> 11:37.208
His name's Keith.

11:37.208 --> 11:39.458
I hightailed it outta there
when I was 12.

11:39.458 --> 11:42.458
-♪ Ooh love hurts ♪

